    Direct Known Subclasses:
    NEATNeuronAllele, NEATSynapseAllele

    public class NEATAllele<G extends NEATGene>
extends VectorAllele<G>
implements java.lang.Comparable<NEATAllele<G>>

    Base class for representations of NEAT alleles.

    Sub-classes must implement a copy-constructor that accepts a single parameter which is the allele to copy, and which should generally just call super() with the allele to copy. See com.ojcoleman.europa.configurable.PrototypeBase#Prototype(PrototypeBase).

    Author:
    O. J. Coleman

    • Field Detail

      • enabled

        protected boolean enabled
        When false indicates that the allele/gene pair is disabled in the alleles genotype and should not be expressed in the phenotype. For a neuron this means the neuron and all its pre and post synapses will not be expressed. For synapses it means the single synapse will not be expressed.
